            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-09T13:00:00-05:00" n="771" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>In telegram 259, July 7, 3 p.m., from Batavia, Mr. Foote reported formation of a
                    new Indonesian Cabinet on July 3, with the Defense Minister, Dr. Sjarifoeddin,
                    also as Prime Minister; and with the Vice Minister for Foreign Affairs, Hadji
                    Agoes Salim, as Foreign Minister. The latter would head the delegation to
                    negotiate with the Dutch. (856E.00/7–747)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
